sequenceDiagram
    participant DS as deploy.sh<br/>(Init Container)
    participant API as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OP as opendatahub operator<br/>(KfDef Controller)
    participant Dashboard as rhods-dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NBC as odh-notebook-controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelCtrl as odh-model-controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant MM as modelmesh-controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DSPO as data-science-pipelines-operator<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant Alert as Alertmanager<br/>10443/TCP HTTPS
    participant BB as Blackbox Exporter<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS
    participant ClusterProm as OpenShift Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant PD as PagerDuty API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DMS as Dead Man's Snitch<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant SMTP as SMTP Server

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over DS,API: Flow 1: Platform Bootstrap Deployment
        DS->>API: Create namespace: redhat-ods-applications<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        DS->>API: Create namespace: redhat-ods-monitoring<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        DS->>API: Create namespace: rhods-notebooks<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        DS->>API: Apply Dashboard CRDs<br/>(OdhApplication, OdhDocument, OdhQuickStart, OdhDashboardConfig)
        DS->>API: Apply ISV Application Tiles<br/>(Jupyter, Anaconda, OpenVINO, etc.)
        DS->>API: Apply NetworkPolicies + RBAC bindings
        DS->>API: Apply KfDef CRs (dashboard, nbc, modelmesh, dspo, notebooks, monitoring, anaconda)
        API-->>OP: KfDef CR triggers reconciliation
        OP->>API: Deploy components from odh-manifests
        API-->>Dashboard: Dashboard deployed
        API-->>NBC: Notebook controller deployed
        API-->>ModelCtrl: Model controller deployed
        API-->>MM: ModelMesh deployed
        API-->>DSPO: DSPO deployed
        DS->>API: Apply monitoring stack manifests<br/>(Prometheus, Alertmanager, Blackbox)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Prom,SMTP: Flow 2: Prometheus Monitoring (Managed Service)
        Note over Prom: Init containers poll for component readiness<br/>(230 retries x 10s = ~38min max wait)
        Prom->>Dashboard: Health check<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
        Prom->>NBC: Health check<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>ModelCtrl: Health check<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>MM: Health check<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>DSPO: Health check<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Note over Prom: All components ready - start scraping
        Prom->>ClusterProm: Federation scrape<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
        Prom->>NBC: Metrics scrape<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>ModelCtrl: Metrics scrape<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>MM: Metrics scrape<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>DSPO: Metrics scrape<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        Prom->>BB: Probe targets<br/>9115/TCP HTTP
        BB->>Dashboard: Endpoint probe<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
        Note over Prom,Alert: SLO burn rate alert fires
        Prom->>Alert: Alert notification
        Alert->>PD: Critical alert<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Service Key
        Alert->>DMS: Heartbeat watchdog<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: URL Token
        Alert->>SMTP: Email notification<br/>STARTTLS<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    end
